node.text:
My New Show Better Human Better Dog premieres on National Geographic!

30 years ago I came to America to become the best dog trainer in the world
I had a dream and that dream has transformed into a new mission.

A mission to make this world a better planet by bettering the way we as humans treat our animals through a natural, simple, and profound approach. 

I am so excited for you all to see my new show. 

This is a video about me and my story. 

Blessings ❤️

#betterhumansbetterplanet

This is a video honoring my best friend, Junior Millan.

Thank you for 15 years of Trust, Respect, and Love.

Rest in Peace, Junior Millan.

#betterhumansbetterplanet

node.text:
Remember to allow the dog to come to you.

Stay calm and confident. Then claim your space.

The dog will then come to you and eventually relax in front of you. This is the time to give the dog affection.

A dog learns Nose, Eyes, and Ears.

It is important to practice No Touch, No Talk, No Eye Contact!

Cesar Millan: Better Human Better Dog premieres Friday at 9/8c on National Geographic. @natgeotv 

#betterhumansbetterplanet #dogtraining #trainingtiptuesday

node.title: Training Tip Tuesday: How To Properly Greet A Dog! 🐕

node.text:
In this episode, I help a couple whose German Shepherd won't calm down.

The couple is 6 months pregnant and wants to prepare their German shepherd for their child.

Watch how I am able to address this issue and be sure to stay tuned for my new show premiering July 30, 2021 on National Geographic. 

Remember if you control the nose of a dog you control 60% of the brain.

We use food to demonstrate how to create rules, boundaries, and limitations.

It is crucial to develop these rules around food.

Calm and Confident.

Full Video on YouTube!

#betterhumansbetterplanet

node.title: How To Develop Boundaries around Food with your Dog! (Dog Nation Shorts)

node.text:
My Dog Chases Everything! What should I do?

In this Live Demonstration, I teach how it is important to stop the excitement before it happens.

Remember it is important to know how to use the tools we have in order to create the outcome we want.

It is our job as the Pack Leader to calm our dogs down if they enter a frantic state of mind.

Learn more of my natural, simple, profound approach @trainingcesarsway

#betterhumansbetterplanet #dogtraining #dog

node.text:
🐕

Remember it is important to exercise your dogs! This is a great tool to use, but there are also many other ways.

How do you exercise your dogs? Comment 👇🏼 and let us know what works for you.

My @trainingcesarsway team and I show this during demos in the TCW program.

Thx @jasonderulo @jenafrumes and your pack for letting me show you this #dogtraining tip. What inspired me to do this years ago was the TV show, The Jetsons! and Astro their dog was always on a treadmill.

#betterhumanbetterplanet

node.text:
In this Dog Nation Episode, I help Victor and Anngel Benoun, with their dog Fergus. Fergus is a golden retriever who is a burn survivor. Fergus has one issue, he is aggressive on the leash.

Whenever he sees a dog he lunges and barks. This is a very dangerous situation.

Can I help solve this case?

Remember it is important to be calm and confident as the pack leaders of our dogs!

Our dogs need to FOLLOW us not LEAD us.

Full Video on YouTube!

#betterhumansbetterplanet

Happy 4th of July! 🎇

#betterhumansbetterplanet

node.text:
My New Show Better Human Better Dog premieres on National Geographic!

30 years ago I came to America to become the best dog trainer in the world
I had a dream and that dream has transformed into a new mission.

A mission to make this world a better planet by bettering the way we as humans treat our animals through a natural, simple, and profound approach. 

I am so excited for you all to see my new show. 

This is a video about me and my story. 

Blessings ❤️

#betterhumansbetterplanet

node.text:
Remember to allow the dog to come to you.

Stay calm and confident. Then claim your space.

The dog will then come to you and eventually relax in front of you. This is the time to give the dog affection.

A dog learns Nose, Eyes, and Ears.

It is important to practice No Touch, No Talk, No Eye Contact!

Cesar Millan: Better Human Better Dog premieres Friday at 9/8c on National Geographic. @natgeotv 

#betterhumansbetterplanet #dogtraining #trainingtiptuesday

node.text:
In this episode, I help a couple whose German Shepherd won't calm down.

The couple is 6 months pregnant and wants to prepare their German shepherd for their child.

Watch how I am able to address this issue and be sure to stay tuned for my new show premiering July 30, 2021 on National Geographic. 

Remember if you control the nose of a dog you control 60% of the brain.

We use food to demonstrate how to create rules, boundaries, and limitations.

It is crucial to develop these rules around food.

Calm and Confident.

Full Video on YouTube!

#betterhumansbetterplanet

node.text:
In our newest YouTube vlog, we welcome Jason Derulo & Jena Frumes to the ranch whose Belgian Malinois won't stop pulling on the leash.

We go over the importance of exercise, knowing which tools to use to create the outcome you want, and one creative way to exercise your dogs using the treadmill!

Thank you for visiting, Jason and Jena, we look forward to seeing you soon!

Link in bio!

#betterhumansbetterplanet

node.text:
My Dog Chases Everything! What should I do?

In this Live Demonstration, I teach how it is important to stop the excitement before it happens.

Remember it is important to know how to use the tools we have in order to create the outcome we want.

It is our job as the Pack Leader to calm our dogs down if they enter a frantic state of mind.

Learn more of my natural, simple, profound approach @trainingcesarsway

#betterhumansbetterplanet #dogtraining #dog
